25|$|U-505 {{was kept}} at the navy base in Bermuda and intensively studied by US Navy {{intelligence}} and engineering officers. Some {{of what was}} learned was included in postwar diesel submarine designs. To maintain <b>the</b> <b>illusion</b> <b>that</b> she had been sunk rather than captured, U-505 was painted {{to look like a}} US submarine and renamed as the USS Nemo as not to alert German intelligence that it had been captured.|$|E
